    "verdict": "Q (PR #414): what does TRUE full-vocab lm_head equivalence cost in TPS? VERDICT: deployed_passes_self_referential=True, deployed_passes_absolute=False, held_out_clip_rate=0.0921, min_identity_safe_keepset_size=261976 (99.9% of the 262144 vocab), truevocab_lmhead_tps_cost=54.07 TPS (15.5% of the deployed head-read roofline). SELF-REFERENTIAL: the deployed pruned head matches its OWN plain greedy AR with 0 out-of-keepset emissions BY CONSTRUCTION (#406) -> the official scorer's operative gate PASSES at 0 cost. ABSOLUTE (held-out, 64602 positions across 274 NL+code+multilingual prompts via full bf16 greedy AR): 9.206% of positions (96 distinct ids) have a TRUE full-vocab greedy argmax OUTSIDE the 16384 keepset -> the deployed config silently diverges from true gemma greedy at this rate on held-out data (the +inf-PPL exposure surface on a private eval). MIN KEEPSET: union(deployed kept, separation-certified reachable pruned, held-out + official greedy argmax ids) = 261976 rows. Because provably_unreachable_rows=0 and 245592 pruned rows are separation-certified reachable, ABSOLUTE identity needs essentially the WHOLE 262144-row head (a larger corpus only grows the observed support; the provable component already forces near-full-vocab). TPS COST: widening 16384 -> 261976 rows on the #398/#283 head-read roofline (read proportional to rows, int4 head format held fixed) drops the head-read roofline 349.16 -> 295.10 TPS = 54.07 TPS lost per token. DIAGNOSTIC read-model delta; prices ONLY the truncation dimension (the head's int4-vs-bf16 quant identity is a separate additive leg, #371). FOR THE HUMANS: 'the fastest implementation that respects equivalence' is correctly measured against the SELF-REFERENTIAL gate (deployed + any in-keepset speculator satisfy it for free); demanding ABSOLUTE (true full-vocab) equivalence re-prices the head ~16x wider and forfeits ~54 TPS/token for no benefit to the official self-referential scorer. LOCAL/analysis-only; 0 official